# Session 100 — normalize line endings to LF.
#
# Biome's formatter wants LF; without `.gitattributes` Windows git
# clients silently convert checked-out files to CRLF (via the
# `core.autocrlf=true` default), which then trips the formatter every
# time we run `biome check`. Five files on `main` had accumulated CRLF
# at the time of writing; Session 100 normalized them all in one pass.
#
# This file tells git to store + check out everything as LF
# regardless of the client's `autocrlf` setting, so the formatter and
# the working tree agree.
#
# Override per-extension below if a tool genuinely needs CRLF (none
# today — even `.bat` / `.cmd` shims in `scripts/` work fine as LF on
# Windows in practice).

* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary file types — never touch.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.woff2 binary
*.zip binary
